    <item>
      <title>Social Housing Development Authority (SHDA)</title>
      <link>https://hjacobcarlson.github.io/project/shda/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Nov 2020 18:28:10 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://hjacobcarlson.github.io/project/shda/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Social Housing Development Authority (SHDA) is a proposed new federal institution to address the wave of distressed real estate as a result of the pandemic. The Authority would 1) acquire distressed real estate, 2) rehabilitate the property to livability and environmental standards, and 3) transfer the property to the &amp;ldquo;social housing&amp;rdquo; sector (community land trusts, tenant cooperatives, mission-driven nonprofits, public housing, and others). In doing so, this entity would forestall the scavenging of communities by vulture investors like private equity &amp;ndash; hard lessons we learned from the post-2008 housing crisis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our op-ed on the proposal in the &lt;em&gt;New York Times&lt;/em&gt; can be found &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/03/opinion/affordable-housing-federal-agency.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and a detailed version of can be found &lt;a href=&#34;https://urbandemos.nyu.edu/shda-whitepaper-nov2020/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This proposal is co-authored with &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/gpbaiocchi&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Gianpaolo Baiocchi&lt;/a&gt;, and developed with Marnie Brady, Sara Duvisac, and Ned Crowley, with help from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://urbandemos.nyu.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Urban Democracy Lab&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;coverage&#34;&gt;Coverage&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;print-media&#34;&gt;Print media&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FE6svJ4-QrOYxGW0tUEQ1C_eCAXSW_c3F2lyOA-1o2w/edit&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Letter to Majority Leader Schumer, 1/26/2021&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.oecd-forum.org/posts/a-wealthy-nation-of-the-homeless-the-united-states-eviction-crisis&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;A Wealthy Nation of the Homeless: The United States’ Eviction Crisis&amp;rdquo;, &lt;em&gt;OECD Forum&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.politico.com/news/magazine/2021/01/20/president-biden-administration-unity-healing-policies-experts-ideas-inauguration-roundup-460470&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Biden Wants to Unite the Country. How Can He Do It?&amp;rdquo;, &lt;em&gt;Politico&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.lohud.com/story/news/2020/12/21/ny-renters-face-pandemic-eviction/3945132001/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;NY renters face pandemic evictions ahead of Christmas, even with moratorium. What to know.&amp;rdquo;, &lt;em&gt;LoHud.com&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
